parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended opening of the tailgate can cause loss of cargo, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The tailgate opens unintentionally
the tailgate falls while driving
the tailgate does not stay up
the tailgate unlocks randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, such as brakes, engine, and transmission, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle slows down or stops suddenly
the brakes fail
the engine stalls
the transmission slips
the radio and lights malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions, accidents, or injuries, especially if the driver is unable to control the volume or access important safety features.
symptoms: The volume increases suddenly
the radio turns on unexpectedly
the audio system malfunctions
the Bluetooth connection fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when towing heavy trailers.
symptoms: The trailer brakes disable or malfunction
the driver information center displays error messages
the trailer brakes disengage unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause accidents, injuries, or strandings, especially if the vehicle loses power while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails
the vehicle loses power
the engine misfires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels hard or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake warning lights appear on the dashboard
"Brake System Failure" message is displayed
limited braking ability
and loss of power-assisted brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the integrated trailer brake system can cause the loss of trailer braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: "Trailer Brake Disabled" or "Trailer Brake Failure" message is displayed
trailer brakes do not function
and warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected increase in volume can cause distraction, panic, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The radio volume suddenly increases to maximum level
the power button and volume controls do not respond
and the volume can only be turned down by rapidly turning the volume knob counter-clockwise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The trailer brake system disables
the "Trailer Brakes Disabled Service Required" message appears on the driver information panel
and the trailer brakes do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reflection of the interior trim pieces can cause distraction, blind spots, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The interior trim pieces reflect sunlight into the driver's eyes
causing blind spots and obstructing the view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle fire can cause serious injuries, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: Flames appear in the rear of the vehicle
and the vehicle becomes fully engulfed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust leak and CO2 buildup can cause health problems, dizziness, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: High CO2 levels in the cabin
exhaust leak
and potential health problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Remote Start and Engine Running Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine running while the vehicle is turned off can cause safety issues, CO2 buildup, and potentially lead to fires.
symptoms: The engine continues to run after the vehicle is turned off
and the air conditioning system remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unfulfilled recall and accessory issues can cause safety problems, inconvenience, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The recall is not fulfilled
and the accessory (sports bar with chimsl accessories high brake light) is not installed or functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and hard shifting can cause loss of power, difficulty accelerating, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slipping
hard shifting
jerking
lunging
or hesitation when shifting gears
especially when accelerating or decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear vision camera system can cause safety concerns when reversing, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rearview camera display screen goes blank with an error message
or the camera system malfunctions intermittently when in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical and mechanical issues can cause the vehicle to become disabled, making it difficult or impossible to shift into neutral, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle becomes disabled due to an electrical or mechanical issue
making it impossible to shift into neutral
and the vehicle shifts into park
leaving no way to move the vehicle safely off the roadway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4WD system can cause safety concerns when driving in inclement weather, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The 4WD system warning message appears
and the vehicle is unable to engage 4WD in inclement weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DEF system can cause the vehicle to enter reduced power mode, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The DEF tank needs to be replaced due to a bad sensor or module
and the vehicle is unable to operate normally.
